The group called Against the West tweeted: "The following have just been hacked: Russian Space Forces, Ministry of Transport of Russia, AIP of the Russian Federation, Russia Air." They added: "Hello. We've returned and are now actively working with Anonymous and some other groups in the Russian campaign. We stand with Ukraine and its allies." Ukraine has called on cyber-hackers to defend against Russia. The government of Ukraine put the call out for volunteers from the country's hacker underground to help protect critical infrastructure and conduct cyber spying missions against Russian troops. As Russian forces attacked cities across Ukraine, requests for volunteers began to appear on hacker forums on Thursday morning. The post read: "Ukrainian cybercommunity! "It's time to get involved in the cyber defense of our country." The news comes after Russian state TV channels have been hacked by Anonymous. The cyber hackers changed the state broadcast to show a different view of the Ukraine conflict. Anonymous tweeted: "Russian state TV channels have been hacked by Anonymous to broadcast the truth about what happens in Ukraine."